# Mutter problems in GNOME 3.26 (Wayland) with 2 graphic cards

  'Can't initialize KMS backend: could not find drm kms'

  Solution: Add 'MUTTER_ALLOW_HYBRID_GPUS=1' to /etc/environment.
  
# ACPI Warnings in dmesg:

  'ACPI Warning: SystemIO range 0x0000000000000428-0x000000000000042F conflicts with OpRegion 0x0000000000000400-0x000000000000047F (\PMIO) (20170728/utaddress-247)'
  
  * Blacklist some modules in /etc/modprobe.d
  
    /etc/modprobe.d/blacklist.conf
      blacklist pcspkr
      blacklist lpc_ich
      blacklist gpio-ich
      
  * Rebuild initramfs
  
  
 # Intel i915 errors in dmesg:
  '[drm:intel_set_cpu_fifo_underrun_reporting [i915]] *ERROR* uncleared fifo underrun on pipe A
   [drm:intel_cpu_fifo_underrun_irq_handler [i915]] *ERROR* CPU pipe A FIFO underrun
   [drm:intel_set_pch_fifo_underrun_reporting [i915]] *ERROR* uncleared pch fifo underrun on pch transcoder A
   [drm:cpt_irq_handler [i915]] *ERROR* PCH transcoder A FIFO underrun'
   
   * Special kernel parameter: intel_iommu=on
   * Using integradted i7-3770 igfx with KMS and no intel driver
   
   No solution yet (Kernel 4.14.15-1).

